License
=======

This project is dual-purpose: it is intended both as a standalone tool and as an
upstream contribution to the Nmap Scripting Engine.

NSE components (for upstream compatibility)
-------------------------------------------
The following files are offered under the same terms as Nmap itself (the Nmap Public
Source License, NPSL — see https://nmap.org/npsl/), so they can be contributed to and
redistributed within the Nmap project:

    scripts/mcp-info.nse
    scripts/mcp-enum.nse
    scripts/mcp.lua
    nmap-service-probes.mcp

Each NSE file carries the standard header line:
    "Same as Nmap--See https://nmap.org/book/man-legal.html"

